+Addressed in `src/policy/preview.py`. The fallback payload now preserves both `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` when `preview_enabled` is `False`, so the reopened preview-unavailable case keeps `human_review_required` instead of dropping review metadata.
+
+T-214-02
+
+Marked duplicate of `T-214-01`. It points at the same reopened fallback regression and is covered by the same payload fix.
+
+T-214-03
+
+Not applied. This thread is obsolete on the current branch because it targets an outdated diff hunk and would revive legacy behavior that should remain removed.
+
+T-214-04
+
+Addressed in `tests/test_preview.py`. Added a regression that exercises `build_policy_preview(..., approval_state="manual_review", preview_enabled=False, ...)` and asserts the fallback payload keeps `approval_state="human_review_required"` with `requires_human_review == True`.
+
+T-214-05
+
+Addressed in `docs/approval_policy.md`. The fallback response example now shows the corrected payload, including `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`.
